COVID-19 Status

As of 3:03PM PT today, over 1.6 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 26.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 11.6 thousand new infections were reported and -1141 deaths. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 54.7 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 85.5% have their 1st shot and 78.6% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 9.1 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~107 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Nov-19 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
